Patch Set 3: Do not merge

Um, let's not add that header support. There is no reason for it when you can just use content-length (and since we don't pass metadata in headers in v2.)

Patch Set 3:

Hey Mark,

We still need a means for the client to provide the image size if chunked transfer is being used i.e. if content-length is not/cannot be set. In this case, as implemented in 1220197, the glanceclient allows for the caller to pass in a value for x-meta-image-size. If there is another/better way to do it please let me know but i do think we should include this somehow since have to revert to the slower resize-befoe-write is really non-optimal.

Patch Set 3:

Hi Ed,

After reading Mark's comment very quickly (and perhaps not following all the subtleties) I think what he's is saying is:

1) if you know the size in advance use Content-Length and do not use transfer encoding.

This will require a change in common/http.py to detect the presence of the content length header and if present switch to not use chunked transfer encoding

2) if you don't know the size in advance then don't supply a content-length header, and use chunked transfer encoding

'x-image-meta-size' is a v1 concept and is unlikely to get approved in v2.
